    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -847.2095037880637,
        -245.72214280920628
      ],
      "size": [
        560,
        650
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 4,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Chest / upper torso masked inpaint A/B test\n\nShared upstream:\n\n- Same original image.\n- Mask is painted directly on the original `LoadImage` node with ComfyUI's built-in Mask Editor.\n- Same FLUX2 model, CLIP, VAE, prompt, seed, sampler, scheduler, and image reference latent.\n\nHow to create the mask:\n\n1. Right-click `Original image + built-in mask editor`.\n2. Choose `Open in Mask Editor`.\n3. Paint the chest / upper torso area.\n4. Save the mask.\n5. The node's `MASK` output feeds both A/B branches.\n\nBranch A tests the classic ComfyUI path:\n\n`InpaintModelConditioning` -> masked latent -> sampler.\n\nBranch B tests the DA v4.5/v5-style path:\n\n`VAEEncode original` -> `SetLatentNoiseMask` -> `ReferenceLatent` on positive/negative -> sampler.\n\nMask rules:\n\n- White = editable chest / upper torso / shirt region.\n- Black = protected.\n- Keep face, hair, and neck black if possible.\n- Include enough surrounding shirt / torso context for fabric tension.\n\nThe outputs are saved separately and batched as original, A, B."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
